caption: Consistent. I go here for the same dish. It’s one of my favorites and it’s always the same. Well.... except I swear the croquettes were bigger last year.

We were expecting something special since this place was featured on Guy Fieri's Diners, Drive-ins, and Dives. The service was very friendly, helpful, and accommodating. The croquetas were quite tasty and fun. We were not impressed with the rest of the food. It was good and hot and fresh, but not great. There wasn't as much flavor in the spicy lamb grinder as you'd expect. The chorizo was tasty, but overpowered by the bread. The baguettes were good, but too overpowering for the sandwiches. The meats were too dry for the baguettes and not flavorful enough. So, good food, great service, but for the price I won't go back.
One of the coolest local spots in town.
We must have got bad lamb. It was definitely off but the bar is cool.
Delicious food and great laid back environment.
Small restaurant with friendly staff and attentive service.

Nice small, cozy place. After searching for places in Boise that Guy Fieri had visited, we settled on this one because we had always wanted to try Basque food because of our Basque heritage. Lamb stew was very hearty and good as were the croquetas that come with it. Service was friendly.

Absolutely amazing fried peppers. Staff is amazing and helped us make gluten free choices ... Including hard cider .. and they have a good selection! I got the Solomo pork sandwich, on a plate, no bread and it was delicious with a really good pickle on the side and a side of a delicious soup. My fiancee got a lamb stew that was also delicious but I felt the lamb was a bit more like mutton, but he loved it. Rice pudding a must. Very cool atmosphere. The food is amazing!! Come here and experience authentic Basque food!
Great wines, great food, and great service!
Great atmosphere and food!
Good food, great service, and I enjoyed my time.

The Basque Market employee recommended this place to us, they were right on. It really reminded me of places I enjoyed in Europe. Humble and caring service, great food, unbelievable we fed 4 adults and 3 children authentic European cuisine for lunch for only$60. Even my wife was impressed (her dad was a restauranteur). We wish there were more places like this around instead of the corporate places. Next time we're up from California I have it on the list. We don't drink alcohol so for the"bar" part look at other reviews.
Excellent croquettas and lamb grinder. They have a bigger food menu in the restaurant then what is listed on their website.
Great pub food! Great service! Triple D never dissappoints!!!
Croquetas and a Lamb Grinder! My favorite downtown lunch. Outdoor seating, awesome staff...What's NOT to love
Food was great, drinks were great, atmosphere was cozy and lovely, and all for a great price. What more could you want? Definitely come in for some Sidra!

This is one of our favorite places and town and personally think they have the best croquetas in town. The staff are always friendly and welcoming and the restaurant is cozy and wonderful. They also have a great selection of tap beers!

This place is popular for certain. We went in early on a Saturday evening and nearly all the tables were full, inside and out. The food was good, the restaurant clean. Food came quickly. The biggest struggle we had was parking and of course that isn't the fault of the restaurant.
Food was great and they had two towns which is always good. Chris was awesome! would recommend 10/10
Has done a great job with outdoor seating and spacing the tables out to accommodate 2020...as always food, people and location are excellent
Absolutely delicious lamb stew and lamb grinders. Highly recommend the food and the service.
The staff and food are always welcoming. Thank you for taking precautionary steps for health and safety and thank you for filling my belly!
The lamb grinder was amazing! Fast service, nice patio, affordable, and good beer!! (Croquettes in the picture)
Best lamb grinder in the entire country !
Great food!

Quaint little pub with a simple Basque inspired pub food menu. The vibe is similar to an old-school small town pizzaria, where one guy is behind the counter quietly making all the food while another guy takes the orders and delivers the food and drinks while making nice with all the customers. The food (lamb stew and chorizo baguette) was good for bar food.
Great basque dishes, beer offerings, and friendly staff. My group had the tuna sany, lamb sany, peppers, and croquettes. All were freshly prepared and tasty.

Great environment, Fantastic food. What it lacks in sprawling open space, it more than makes up for with it's fantastic basque dishes, and you can't beat the price! There's nothing like great food that doesn't hurt your wallet. I highly recommend the coquetas and lamb stew!
Patio, sunshine, good beer, and great Basque food!
Food is consistently good and service with a smile
Get the croquetas and thank me later
Lamb grinder, need I say more???
Food was good, wine was good! Will definitely go back when I'm in town!
Very tasty food at reasonable prices. Expect to wait for seating,  but it is worth it! I had the lamb stew - very tasty.  Don't miss the  croquetas. Great draft beer options
Excellent quaint location with friendly staff.
Excellent. Best food and service in Idaho❤
Always great.  The croqettas were delicious, as was the solomo sandwich.  Good beer selection too
This was a wonderful basket experience for my husband and I
Wow. Just wow Boise. You really came through. Basque! Wave of the future man

A must see while you are in Boise.  The heart of the Basque block, Bar Gernika has a delicious menu, good tap selection, a fun space and great service.  Everything on the menu is delicious but the apple and cheese plate with some Basque beer is a great way to warm up to the evening or finish it off.
Great food. Fast service
Great food and a nice atmosphere. It gets really busy during lunch time so arrive early if you want a table.
Kabobs had a vinegar taste

Fantastic place! Found this little gem on Diners, Drive-ins & Dives site = so happy! Delicious Basque food - had spicy lamb grinder with homemade croquetas + a fairly local IPA. Attentive prompt service + jam packed by 6pm by locals in the know.
The Basque place. Always pecked!
If you your in Boise and haven't tried this place your missing out!
Loved this little pub downtown Boise Idaho. Lamb sandwich was delicious and home cut fries were to die for. Thank you Bar Gernika
Three words: spicy lamb grinder
Old School Basque Bar. & The Crocettas are the Best
Friendly staff, hearty comfort food, and tasty drinks.
Croquettes and a tuna melt sandwich: Yes plxx.
Croquetas & Beer - what's not to love? It is a bit cramped and so can get busy quickly on weekends, but is a great choice for an early or late meal.
Staff is awesome. Food is great. Relaxed.

Quintessential Boise, a must visit at least once but we have been here many times. Always fun, good service, good food, good drink choices. Historic setting in the heart of downtown. Try everything on the menu !
Best Croquettas in town. Servers are exceptional. Beer on tap is always on the wall so you're never guessing. Highly recommend.
Delicious fair with helpful friendly staff
Great little place for a beer and a snack.
Come here for delicious soup, lamb grinders, cozy your grandma's kitchen atmosphere, and friendly service. One of my favorite spots in Boise 💖
Grateful food, cramped quarters
Great service and food with good prices. A comfy place to relax.
Spicy lamb sandwich always hits the spot. So yummy and tons of food in the portions, also the croquetas are a must!
Food is excellent
It just wasn’t for me
Great atmosphere!  Loved the food and beverages.  Patio is pet friendly.
Anywhere with no TVs and a subscription to The Economist is automatically my favorite bar. Oh yeah, and delicious croquetas
This is my favorite little Basque spot for lunch. Easy to access and everything I've tried on the menu is delicious..dining alone ? Great bar top seating also
Spicy Lamb Grinder great!
This is a nice old style Basque bar. There is a grill right behind the bar and you can order food. Nice selection of beers on tap. I had a cup of soup that was delicious.
Perfect service with difficult customers!  The lamb was cooked to perfection !!!
Delicious Basque food.
When you walk in you'll immediately think dive. But give it a chance the staff is awesome, top quality croquettes and good beer. Can't beet it when you in the mood for some Basque food.

One of my fave places! The croquetas taste like Thanksgiving heaven in your mouth! I'm a big fan on all their veggie dishes, as they're always fresh and grilled to perfection! Service is always good, fast, and tolerates my silly group!
Fantastic patio and great service!
Wonderful food and fun drinks
Super friendly service, fabulous food...mushrooms were FANTASTIC!!

Cool Bar in the Basque Block, had The Spicy Grinder with Tortilla De Patatas.  Grinder was not very spicy but food. service and atmosphere were all good.  Definitely worth checking out if you have not been there.
The spicy lamb is insane!!!! I liked with the spicy chili sauce and then in the au jus.. place had a great vibe, cook was a great dude, hilarious. 40/10
Excellent food as always!
GREAT service, outdoor seating, and a variety of Basque food and drinks available!
Began happy hour! Finally! Looking forward to what's next in the vegan line up.

I just love this place! It's been a favorite of my,m family's for years. Food is amazing (croucettas are my favorite!) and the service is great. Housed in one of the oldest buildings in downtown Boise this place has a lot of character. Wheelchair accessibility inside is a little tight due to,the age of the building; staff & patrons are great about shifting furniture, etc.
V interesting and unusual food! Great service
I love this place it's very cozy with great stew!! I would really recommend it
The food was AMAZING. My husband and I shared a Lamb Grinder and an order of Croquettas. My only issue was there wasn't enough room in my tummy to eat more.
An excellent experience.  Great service and delicious food. You must try it.
Go to their website and look at the pictures of the food pictures worth a thousand words there's a book there
Great food, great service!
Best chill out Basque joint in boise

Lamb grinder and croquetas! Better bar food you’ll not find and the atmosphere in the Basque Block and this bar is just fun. Great place to grab a bite and a beer before or after an event downtown. Fast friendly service. If lamb isn’t your thing but you like sausage check out the double solomo.
Wonderful food, really warm atmosphere. Loved it
Excellent food. Staff was great giving me ideas on what to try.

This place was excellent! Pretty small, so if you come with a big group during busy hours you may have to wait, but as a party of two, we were seated almost instantly during the lunch rush. We came on Saturday, so we ordered the beef tongue special, so so good! Also had the lamb grinder sandwich, freaking excellent. Great fries and amazing croquetas. Pour a little or a lot of that dank hot sauce at the table on just about anything for some added flavor and a little spice. If we ever come back to Boise, we will definitely be coming here.
Customer service and food was great!
This place is always the best.

if you're going to go to Boise, this is the best restaurant in town. I know there are higher rated looking places on Yelp. However this is the real gem. Basque food is not something you're going to find very often.

We had lunch here during the Basque Block Festival.  Even though the place was crowded we had fast and courteous service.  The Solomo and croquettes were delicious and served hot.  Wonderful selection of local beers.  This place has been around for some time giving it a little of the old world charm.  We will definitely be back.
Solomo was delicious.
Service was awesome and the food was better.
James the cook was awesome! Super funny and great to talk to!
The staff was very friendly and sweet , the food is tasty, better than most other options around. Worth the drive & task of finding parking.
The service was friendly and the food was good
Food was good, service was gruff, bar was very small.
The food was amazing and great hospitality. My mother and I were visiting from Nevada and my brother wanted us to try his "favorite Basque place". It really was!
Short, but eclectic tap list, tasty fun food (like beef tongue lunch Saturday), and a cozy dive atmosphere. Fantastic patio.
Was okay. loved the fries.

When we arrived, the place was happily crowded and booming with activity. The staff was slammed and working as fast as they could. In spite of this, we received immediate attention, and our drinks were served very quickly. We had to wait a bit for the food, but our very efficient server told us that would be the case. When it finally came, we were more than pleased. The croquettes were absolutely delicious. I don't know if they make their own bread or not, but it was to die for! This is clearly a very popular place with the locals and held in high regard. We very much enjoyed our experience here and would definitely come back. It's great to see a place thriving so much that they probably need to hire more help! Fantastic!
Enjoyed the chorizo sandwich and croquetas

Their "Extra Spicy Lamb Grinder" was the most spicy food I've ever had since living Idaho. What was completely unfair was that it was made soooo good that I felt compelled to finish it... Anyway nice sit down place and went during my 30 minute lunch break with plenty of time left over. Thanks guys!!!
Love this place..great food
Welcoming, friendly staff. Good wine, good beer. Do you need more?

A local treasure in terms of service, food, and drinks. Their lamb grinder is so tender and savory, and the hand-cut fries are always golden perfection. Croquetas are proof of a higher power (be sure to use the Tiger Sauce in the clear bottle on your table for dipping these little spheres of wonder), and if you’ve never had a kalimotxo (kalli-mo-cho) you really should try one.  The portions are generous, the staff is friendly, and the food is delightful.
Always great food and charming atmosphere
Great bar, great food, excellent choice of quality beer. They had Oude Geuze on the menu!
Authentic Basque/Spanish food in a classic Boise setting. Service was a little slow but worth it
Super busy but well worth the wait!!! The house dressing is absolutely amazing! Along with the pickled onions and everything else I ate! Highly recommend!
Good wine and food and patio for people watching!! What a kick that was😀😀
Amazing food, service, and drinks.  We had an awesome time!
Best pub grub. A must stop for visitors to Boise.
AMAZING food on the menu, the bartender was very laid back and kind with all sorts of recommendations, and a constantly rotating selection of beer. A truly wonderful, homey-feeling establishment.

Good food. As I recall (this was a few years back), I had either the lamb dip or the lamb grinder, as well as the lamb stew (on a different occasion). Both recommended. It seems to me I had something else on a third occasion, but I don't remember clearly. Service was good except for one waitress who was putting too much pressure on me to drink. I know it's a bar, but it's also one of the better restaurants in downtown Boise, so some people are going to go there who don't necessarily want to drink. (The Hall & Oates that was playing when I walked in took me back to my real home town of Philadelphia.)
Great little bar in downtown.
Authentic
Food is amazing as always. Staff is just outstanding. Wish I had one where I live so I can spend all my money there
A great beer selection coupled with very tasty sandwiches. Good deal!
Wonderfully quaint Basque bar with excellent food and good service. The Spicy Lamb Grinder  is excellent. The fries are hand cut.
Loved the atmosphere. The bartender was great.
Great food, great service!

I loved the feel of this place, kind of  like a worn in pair of jeans.  Great Basque influenced pub food, fun wine and beer, awesome value, friendly service.  I would eat here once or twice a week if I lived in Boise.

It is my all time favorite restaurant in Boise! A spicy lamb grinder with a side of croquettes is a must! They have delicious options for vegetarians as well. The beer list and tap options are great, as well as wine. The building itself is historic and really fun to check out while you wait for your food/drinks. Enjoy!

Our table had croquettes, lamb kabob, lamb grinder, chorizo sandwich and jalapeno potato soup.  I felt like quality ingredients were used and the meal was prepared with care.  The croquettes were a delightful surprise.  I was disappointed with the level of flavor in the dishes.  The flavors were so subtle and my limited experience with Basque food is that it has a robust, rather than bland, flavor.  If you are sensitive to noise, be aware that the building acoustics lend toward a loud environment.
Authentic Basque pub. Get the croquetas and a lamb grinder. You won't be sorry! The mushrooms appetizer is great too. Always great food and great service at Bar Gernika.
Quaint spot, busy every time I go. Small venue, so not always great for larger groups.great vibe.
Local Basque bar with best croquetas in town!!!
Ordered a lamb grinder and it was dry and had no flavor, server didn’t seem to notice or care I hadn’t touched my food except for one bite. The croquettas were decent
I always enjoy my visits to the Bar! I tried a sandwich I'd never had, love the croquettes, had a wonderful cheese plate, and they converted me to an ardour for Basque Ciders!
Delicious food and friendly staff! Well worth a wait if you were to have one
Delicious food, great service, neat atmosphere
Yummy Basque food in downtown Boise!
Decent place!
Small, cozy place with excellent service, drinks, and food. Loved it!
Nothing else like it in Boise. Hit it early on Saturday for the Beef Tongue. Don't forget a refreshing Kalimotxo.

I've been here twice more than year apart and every experience was great. Wines are good, food is excellent, and the service is incredibly considerate. It's always pretty full to packed because the prices and service are fantastic. I have tried several things on the menu (the small things usually because the tapas here is great) and I have enjoyed every single one. Tortilla, solomo sandwich, the chorizo, the croquettes = fantastic each time. Generous wine pours. So much love for this place, I try to make it my first meal in Boise now. Prices are also incredibly good. Went with friend and for $50 we had 3 glasses of wine each, and 4 tapas plates. I am so incredibly full right now, happy and tipsy
Great selection of wines, unreal food, for the space they have, knowledgable staff.
This was good! Chill atmosphere and laid back food. The croquettes were to die for! Sandwiches are large and flavorful. Try the brown spicy sauce!
Best beef tongue! Must try Calimocho!!!!
The croquettes are what I come here for. Love them with the tiger sauce. The staff is friendly and the food is on point.
Love this place. Got to have the flan.
Is this really basque food? It was good, but based off other basque restaurants I’ve been too it’s not that great.

Awesome little spot to stop in to try some Basque food and some great craft beers as well. The. Soup of the day was sweet potato bisque and it was great creamy and delicious. I also got an order the croquetas and they are amazing anyone who comes here needs to try them so good. The chorizo sandwich was also very good great bread with a tasty sausage. I also had to try the kalimotxo drink which is half red wine half come it was interesting not my thing but not bad either.
Delicious and amazing

The spicy lamb grinder and a cup of the jalapeno potato soup, with a side of croquetas were amazing. The au jus or gravy, whatever you'd like to call it, depending where you are from was so wonderful I was tempted to drink it straight from the cup. It was a busy night so the service was a little slow, nothing a cold beer couldn't solve though.

Bar Gernika is busy on the weekends for a reason. It's a really great place to get a bite and drink a few microbrews. The Extra Spicy Lamb Grinder is my favorite. It is really spicy. It doesn't compete with the triple habanero from Flying Pie, but I think it my be close to the single habanero. It's definitely an experience. They have a lot of other delicious options, if you aren't a pepper-gut. If you do crave something hot, lamb pairs really well with spice.

I've been coming here when I'm in Boise for years now. Never disappoints. Little hole in the wall bar that serves delicious Basque food (the croquetas are to die for, Saturdays they have beef tongue that is incredible). AND some of the best beer available on tap in Boise.

Always the best! We drive across town to eat at Bar Gernika. They always have good beers and excellent food. The atmosphere is so comfortable. Add to all that a superb staff, and it's easy to order just one more drink just to stay a little longer. I love this place!!

A nice hometown bar with an ethnic (Basque) flavor. It isn't large. The prices are reasonable. The staff is friendly. I suggest ordering the croquettes, which are not available at most other bars and restaurants.

It's Boise's old world pub with great food and beer. It's small but its warm colors from the exposed brick and the feel from the plaster & timber walls give it it's charm like your in a English/European pub.  The food is based on Basque flavors. The beers are from a mix of local and abroad breweries. Check out the beer list for some really hard to find bottles.  Prices are more than fair.  If you leave this place with out at least a side of croquettes you've done something wrong.
Great food. Staff is always friendly. Spicy lamb grinder or kabobs are a great option.
Delicious Basque food and great beer - a Boise classic!
Good Basque food
One of my favorite places in Boise
Great little bar. Excellent beer selection with fantastic hearty food.
I love eating here! Parking can kind of be a pain, but that is no fault of the bar. The food is great, and staff is always friendly
Welcoming, delicious tapas and attentive service.
The soups are always perfect. Almost always get the spicy lamb grinder but have started ordering the tuna melt and it is amazing. Also they have the best flan in Boise.
Holy yum! Eat here, now!
The croquetas are fantastic!
Food is great
A must stop in Boise. Great atmosphere, incredible food. Get there early, it gets busy at lunchtime.
Cozy environment with absolutely delicious food. And it's in the Basque district. Would recommend to anyone visiting Boise.
Loved the food and service. It's a small place but had a nice pub feel. Will definitely go again!

Great Basque restaurant/bar. All ages. Cozy in the heart of Boise's Basque district.  Always order the croquettes! Come here whenever we are in town. Even took some frozen croquettes back on the plane home.
Very slow service.  Waiting for more than one hour to ger plates. Only one person in the kitchen for a full restaurant. CRAZY. Avoid this place.
The food here is fantastic
Excellent food, drinks, and comfy atmosphere. The chorizo sandwich is sublime, protip: add the grilled peppers and onions. Croquetas are a must try.
I love this place. Been coming here since high school and now plan my trips back around the Saturday beef tongue. Beef tongue is a must.
Just passing through Boise, we were very fortunate to have found this place. I felt like I was back in the Basque country. Don't miss it!

Decent beer for decent prices, food just ok, horrible service if you are not a local/frequent customer. The waitress ignored us for close to half an hour after bringing our drinks. She seemed nice enough to the customers she knows, but was downright rude to us. As the food really was nothing to rave about, I would not recommend the place.

Bar Gernika is my favorite pub in Boise. Any time I'm here I feel so welcomed, and I'm always taken care of right away. The food is awesome! Though I haven't tried their whole menu becaue I always get the same thing...spicy lamb grinder with a side of croquettas! Honestly, this place should be even more of a staple to Boise than it already is.
Great basque cuisine.
Our go to place to eat. Everything on the menu is amazing.
Fantastic pub. The menu is full of Basque-inspired items, the beer list is short but always amazing. Order the spicy lamb grinder or lamb stew, either one with croquetas.
Have been going to Gernika for years.  Food is top notch.  Beer selection is always well thought out.  The staff is great.  And it's in a neat historic building.  Highly recommended.
Excellent place! Bustling restaurant with wonderful, friendly service.
Lovingly curated beer selection.
Neighborhood gem. Great selection of food and beer.
Awesome Spicy Lamb Grinder!
Really good food and quaint!
Croquettes are amazing
Get the croquetas. No matter what else you do, get croquetas.
This little hole in the wall has some AWESOME pub food! I'll be bringing my best friend here when he comes to visit! 10/10 would recommend.
Me and my son had a great dinner at this place. We enjoyed the food and the service was friendly and nice. A place to come back.
their croquettes are AMAZING!
Love the Solomo sandwich with  the sidre!
A Boise staple. Be sure to try the beef tongue they serve on Saturdays.
Love it. Love the croquetas!. Open fairly late. Grate beers and snacks. The lamb grinder is amazing as well.

I've been really happy with my visits here, and I really enjoyed sitting on the patio during the Basque Festival this past summer eating good food and being able to watch the events. I had their spicy lamb sandwich and it was delicious. It kind of reminding me of a French dip, but better. They've always got a nice selection of craft brews so there's something for everyone.
The food is really good.
We stop here every time we're in town for the best croquettas and draft beer in Boise. Thumbs way up!
Great neighborhood hangout. The croquetas are wonderful. Great service from Jodi.
Lamb grinder burger is good here
Great service. Great food
Excellent service, great food & cozy, welcoming atmosphere.
Good flavor
Grind lamb burgier is good herr.
Real taste of Basque food in a downtown setting.
Great food good service
Excellent food in an authentic atmosphere.  Definitely should be on your list!
Great place.
Great food, awesome service and fun beer selection. Must have the croquettas, solomo sandwich, chorizo and lamb sandwich.
Lamb grinder is always good. Great little spot with ethnic flavors.
Great food. Loved the spicy lamb grinder .  Good soup and super croqueta. Friendly staff in a quaint s nbn all bar.
Fantastic food and drink! Loved the atmosphere, and we had great service!
Excellent food, superb service
Love

So disappointing! We were sent there by a friend (local) and wow, not what we were expecting. Our waiter was having a really bad day. Super rude. We ordered a cheese plate and 25 min later, we had to complain. Staff was super defensive, no customer service at all. The beer can was dated May, 2018!! We ended up going to Eureka! Much better service.

Horrible, 30 minute wait for cheese platter and restaurant was only a third full. Beer can clearly showed expired. I asked to just pay bill for 2 beers and waiter got in my face. Was close violent. DON'T GO THERE.
One of the best places to meet with friends in the downtown area! Food and drinks are 👌

My wife and I stopped by for dinner while in town and it didn’t disappoint. We started with the Chorizo and Cheese Quesadilla before moving on to Lamb Grinders. My wife enjoyed her wine and I my Kalimotxo. Wait service was Too Notch as well and we will definitely be back when we return to town in October.
Understaffed but great prices and good.
Lamb grinder was amazing.  Service friendly and attentive. Definitely recommend a stop here when in boise!!

Cozy spot with beer on tap and solid food. We kept smelling funnel cakes when walking past this place, and then found out it was the croquetas! Little yummy fried balls of doughy goodness. The cheese plate with chorizo is a meal by itself, …
Nice quaint little restaurant bar.

I've been eating and drinking at Bar Gernika for 15+ years and have never once been disappointed. Expect a super casual, pub-like atmosphere with a beer selection curated by the impeccably discerning owner, with beers that are not always available elsewhere in town. When you arrive, just order the croquettas, don't even bother looking at the menu for them, best in town, and best with tiger sauce on them (you'll find out when you're there).  Otherwise, enjoy a tightly constrained menu of sandwiches, salads and a few entrees.  If you're there to see or be seen, the mayor and other notables from the statehouse frequent the bar stools.
Good food nothing more to be said.
Always a great time with delicious food and great staff. I always make it a point to stop in when in Boise.
Lamb grinder and croquettas! Life changing

Love this place! One of the more unique restaurants in Boise. Cozy, comfortable,  always home cooked food. Not many places like this anymore! Try the croquettes and a spicy lamb grinder, it's why you should be here!

This place should absolutely be visited if you haven't yet! The Basque community has a strong presence in Boise and this establishment does a great job of representing the culture. The food was tasty. The service was first class. The atmosphere was excellent. Renée, Dylan, and Chadwick really went the extra mile to help me get to know the area, it's history, and the bucket list of things only a local could tell you to do. I HIGHLY RECOMMEND you come here for food, drinks, and even a little history at this gem of the Boise community.

DELICIOUS CHORIZO SANDWICH! Chorizo is amazing, bread is amazing, grilled onions and pimentos are amazing! Great local beers and friendly service. Of all the restaurants in Boise, this one is on another level. I would make an effort to come here every time I visited Boise.

This place is just the best. They have fresh beer on tap, large mugs to serve, and absolutely delicious food. It's a little small inside, which can make it crowded. The price of their food is very reasonable, cheap by some people's standards. Highly suggested for daily lunch.

Wanted to try Basque cider and croquetas while in the area and that's what I did. Cider was delicious while croquetas were decent but as as flavourful as I remember them being in Spain and some sauce helped. But still very happy I got to try these out :)
Sooooo good! Crouqutas are my new favorite! I love the lamb grinder and Rainer beer
Amazing as always. Get the lamb grinder and croquettes.
Love this place.  Always have good food and a good time here ❤
Love it! A staple of Boise!
The heart of Boise downtown Basque food.

The spicy lamb grinder was DELICIOUS! They have a good selection of beers. Only problem is the place is incredibly popular and TINY! Pretty much everything I tried was perfect - those little ball things... zomg... fresh cut frys? yeah.... thinly sliced lamb with peppers, cheese, jalapenos,  and more on a hoagie? uh.. yeah!!
Found this quaint bar and fell in love my wife and I couldn't have been happier with their food and local beer selection.

It was an enjoyable experience went here with a coworker for lunch. The atmosphere feels like a pub but also has the added benefit of great food. If I lived in Boise I'd certainly go here more regularly.
Great food and great service.
Good eats
Love Gernika, live the grinders.
Excellent Tuna Melt! Good draft beer, watched some fabulous musicians near by then got hungry - so glad they were open - great service, good food - do it!
Simply one of my favorites. A pub with basque flair.
Missed this place.

Amazing!  We love it and always have and will keep going back.  The chef...the woman is amazing.  The ambience is wonderful and makes me feel warm and fuzzy.  Everyone there is wanting to make your visit wonderful.  We love it!
Great food
Boise's most important culinary and beer-inary treasure. You'll try the croquetas.
